		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />non-anamorphic 2.4:1 that's been letterboxed to 4:3 NTSC should be 124 scanlines per field, AFAICT?<br /><br />I mean, 224 ร4รท3 = 298; 298รท2.4 = 124.<br /><br />180 scanlines per field on 4:3 NTSC would be 16:9 (298รท180) .... so if the source material is 12:5 and it's not anamorphic and it's taking 180 scanlines per field, that has to be cropped from the 12:5 master... unless I'm missing something.

		

		</td>
